<h1>Videos</h1>

<p style="color:#999; font-size:1.05rem; margin-bottom:3rem;">Animated explainers in the style of Dalio's <em>Principles</em> and Thompson's <em>Stratechery</em>. Real code. Real architecture. Real numbers. Short enough to watch on a train.</p>

<div style="margin-bottom:3rem; padding:1.5rem; border:1px solid #222; background:#0a0a0a;">
  <div style="color:#666; font-size:0.85rem; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.1em; margin-bottom:1rem;">Three Series</div>
  <div style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <span style="color:#e8e4de; font-weight:600;">How It Works</span> <span style="color:#555;">&middot; 5-8 min</span><br>
    <span style="color:#888; font-size:0.95rem;">One system per video. Animated architecture + real code walkthrough.</span>
  </div>
  <div style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <span style="color:#e8e4de; font-weight:600;">What I Learned From...</span> <span style="color:#555;">&middot; 3-5 min</span><br>
    <span style="color:#888; font-size:0.95rem;">Personal stories with principles. Vulnerability first, framework second.</span>
  </div>
  <div>
    <span style="color:#e8e4de; font-weight:600;">The Code</span> <span style="color:#555;">&middot; 2-3 min</span><br>
    <span style="color:#888; font-size:0.95rem;">One concept. One code snippet. One principle. Ben Thompson decomposition style.</span>
  </div>
</div>

<ul class="essay-list">
{%- for video in collections.videos %}
  <li>
    <a href="{{ video.url }}">{{ video.data.title }}</a>
    <div class="essay-meta">{{ video.data.series }} &middot; {{ video.data.duration }}{% if video.data.date %} &middot; {{ video.data.date | isoDate }}{% endif %}</div>
  </li>
{%- endfor %}
</ul>
